# Progresive Content Discovery (PCD)

## Core Idea
- dispaly content granularly; no cognetive overload 
- guide the user through the structure
- save the progress; let the user resume where they left off (even without an account)
- use visual indicators to show progress/history (muted display of FTUX & onboarding)
- allow for bookmarking or favoriting specific sections
- Main Stages: FTUX > Sign-Up > Onboarding

## FTUX (First-Time User Experience) with action-oriented funnel
Phase 1) first the user lands on the landing-page; in the background is a guest account created to save PCD stages
- clear & emotional landing-page with some simple choices (action buttons)
- secondary choises: Theme & Language
- scroling down the landing-page is also counting as valid action to trigger next phases
Phase 2) Content Acordion is displayed after the user click on one of the actions buttons

Phase 3) Sign-Up
- after the use has viewed all infos on the landing page, there should be a messge "you are reday for the next steps: sign up and dive in"
- after email confermation user gets first achivment:  PIONIER

Phase 4) Onboarding after the email is confirmed

## Sign-Up
- friction should be as little as possible
- it should feel very save: sign-up via email & OTP
- promiss of no botherring after sign-up; olny user aproved notifications will be sent (accordion in the sign-up form: our phylosophy); phylosophy note is added to the sign-up email "Adjust your notifications settings" with a link to notifications settings page
- UI: form title = forground 'log in' with muted 'or Create Account'; one email field & button 'get access'

## Onboarding
- optional onbaording; user can choose to discover the app on himself or walk the onboarding jorney
- onboarding should be an exiting expirience like a game, not somethin forsed
- onboarding progress is tide to achivments

